{"id":1338,"date":"2011-02-09T06:48:58","date_gmt":"2011-02-09T12:48:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_gets_sharper.php"},"modified":"2011-02-09T06:48:58","modified_gmt":"2011-02-09T12:48:58","slug":"viva_gets_sharper","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_gets_sharper.php","title":{"rendered":"Viva gets Sharper"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_logo.gif\" alt=\"Viva Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>First aired in 1993, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.viva.tv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Viva<\/a> is a music and entertainment channel on German television &mdash; with programming that ranges from <em>Friends<\/em> to <em>America&#8217;s Next Top Model<\/em> to <em>Jackass<\/em> to its own Top 10, Top 50, and Top 100 videos. Originally owned privately, Viva was purchased by MTV Europe in 2004 and since 2000 the channel has been exported to Switzerland, Austria, Hungary, Poland, and the UK. In January Viva launched a new on-air package and identity developed by the internal creative team of MTV Networks Germany.<\/p><!--more--><p>The logo evolution is fairly straightforward: it assumes that its viewers recognize the abstract VIVA letters as a set of triangles and it takes it from a blobby friendly logo to an edgy almost angry logo with really, really sharp points. It does away with differentiating between the &#8220;I&#8221; and &#8220;A&#8221; triangles where before the &#8220;I&#8221; was hollow; this version is more confident that way, again giving its audience credit for knowing what channel has four triangles.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_type.jpg\" alt=\"Viva\" \/><\/p>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_show_logos_lg.jpg\" onclick=\"window.open('https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_show_logos_lg.jpg','popup','width=1050,height=576,scrollbars=no,resizable=yes,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false\"><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/viva_show_logos.jpg\" alt=\"Viva\" border=\"0\"\/><\/a><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Show logos. Click image for bigger view.<\/p>\n<p>The new identity revolves around triangles, and a big triangle helps anchor many of the applications. The above image shows the different show logos, or more like show icons. Individually they are all barely okay, but as a whole they really come together and add to the edgy aesthetic. The type selection is also good, avoiding all the usual sans serif suspects for something less refined (in a good way). Below is a video of how it all comes together.<\/p>\n<iframe src=\"http:\/\/player.vimeo.com\/video\/19205462?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"574\" height=\"323\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\"><a href=\"http:\/\/vimeo.com\/19205462\">VIVA REBRAND 2011<\/a> from <a href=\"http:\/\/vimeo.com\/user5847852\">Dinko Lacic<\/a> on <a href=\"http:\/\/vimeo.com\">Vimeo<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Finally, all good TV identities are to be judged by their on-air application and Viva&#8217;s is f*#king awesome. Yes, that&#8217;s my professional and eloquent critique, and I will leave it at that &mdash; I mean, c&#8217;mon, there is people on fire and people exploding (also in a good way). See for yourself below. For more visuals and stills, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.designmadeingermany.de\/2011\/1170\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Design Made in Germany has most of it<\/a>.<\/p>\n<iframe src=\"http:\/\/player.vimeo.com\/video\/19212548?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"575\" height=\"316\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\"><a href=\"http:\/\/vimeo.com\/19212548\">VIVA REBRAND 2011 &#8211; Show Package Reel<\/a> from <a href=\"http:\/\/vimeo.com\/user5847852\">Dinko Lacic<\/a> on <a href=\"http:\/\/vimeo.com\">Vimeo<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.gravitart.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Oguzhan Ocalan<\/a> for first tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110209_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110209_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110209_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110209_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110209_config_03.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110209_votes_03.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv3\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_start.gif\" alt=\"Voting Begins\" \/>\n<table class=\"table\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n\t<tr valign=\"top\">\n        <!--VOTE CONCEPT-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_col\">\n\t\t\t<div id = \"pollDiv1\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/td>\n        <!--GUTTER-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_gutter\">\n            <img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/gutter.gif\" alt=\" \" \/>\n\t\t<\/td>\n\t\t<!--VOTE EXECUTION-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_col\">\n\t\t\t<div id = \"pollDiv2\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/td>\